        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 19 at 1:20PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 120 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 17
miles south of McCamey, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of east central Pecos
County.

This includes Interstate 10 between mile markers 298 and 309.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
